quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  10,62,"Behold! Verily, the auliya of Allah (protectors and helpers for His System of Guidance) — there is no fear over them and nor they shall go in grief"
  10,63,those who Believed and they had been paying obedience
  10,64,"for them are glad tidings in the life of this world and in the Hereafter. There is no changing for the statements of Allah. This: it is the supreme achievement"
  10,65,"And let not their utterance grieve you. Definitely, the honour — all of it, is for Allah (Alone). He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower"
  10,66,"Behold! Verily, to Allah belongs whosoever is in the heavens and whosoever is on the earth. And do not obey those who invoke besides Allah, the partners. They do not obey except conjecture and nothing they (do) but they harbour delusions"
  10,67,"He it is Who has appointed for you the night so that you may rest therein, and the day as one which makes things visible. Surely, in this are indeed signs for a nation who listen"
  10,68,"They (who have deviated from the Book of Allah) said: “Allah has begotten a son.” His Glory keeps Him absolved of it. He is Free of all needs. To Him belongs what is in the heavens and what is in the earth. For this (false accusation) you have no proof with you. Do you say concerning Allah what you know not"
  10,69,"Say: “Verily, those who forge a lie against Allah will not achieve success\" —"
  10,70,"a brief enjoyment in this world, then unto Us will be their returning place; then We shall make them taste the severest punishment because they used to disbelieve"